<br>
As I think about it, two possibilities come to mind:<br>
<br>
a. - They have somehow nerfed horses - I am doing the bit with turning on horse models and my character models but having the 'LuclinPlayerModels=OFF' string in my EQClient.ini. They might have changed it such that you get sit aggro automatically if you do that, or something. <br>
<br>
b.  Instead it could have something to do with where I was standing. I was standing on the steps of the gallows. I had stood there with a horse before, and done the trials successfully, but with a higher level warrior who had AE taunt.<br>
<br>
So I guess what I want to know is, has anyone else noticed anything about aggro on horses lately, or about good/bad places to stand in the exe trial? <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://communities.msn.com/_Secure/0NgAAALgTbhnGVBOnt1Ath65OTuUgERT7lrmALH6CS3lMy6YzWHOPJ71xKjxBzlfft525tjNZ2xlyIr8c0Az2fQ/Gyorgsig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
